title: For Sale:  LaRue Tactical LT123 Scope Rings
postcontent:
I have a 2 month old set of LT123 rings from LaRue Tactical that I no longer need. These are 30mm rings with the VFZ style mount. Additional info below straight from the LaRue website. Text me at 9one0-six33-2two39 if you are interested. Will ship at buyers expense.

"Standard-height rifle scope rings with QD functionality.
The LT123 rings are ideal when mounting rifle scopes with extra large objective lenses, where clearance is a concern. These 30mm rings attach to any MIL-STD-1913 Picatinny rail, but are the perfect-match for the LT113 on Remington 700 model rifles.

The LT123 positions the centerline of the optic 1.28" above the top of the rail."

"About VFZ™ Mounts:
VFZ™ is a new theory in the concept of clamping accessories to MIL-STD-1913 rails. Instead of using a horizontal cross-bolt, the VFZ™ uses a vertical bolt that draws up a clamping foot against the lower angle of the rail, seating the mount similarly to a fully-closed LaRue lever. Once installed on the firearm, index marks allow the user to remove the mount, then reattach to the same tension, providing unprecedented return to zero for a non-QD-levered mount. The unique vertical alignment of the clamp allows components that are structurally stronger than traditional cross-bolt designs.

Why should I select VFZ™ Mounts instead of a QD Lever Mount?:
If you intend to leave an optic or accessory on a rail for the life of the rifle, the VFZ™ option is for you. The VFZ™ is intended as a longer-term, semi-permanent mounting alternative to our well-known Speed Levers. While both mounts will allow the user to remove the mount from the weapon, reinstall it in the same position, and return to zero, the VFZ™ mount is intended for users that will not need to constantly remove and install their mounts (especially in the field). "

title: For Sale:  Norinco NHM-91 AK47 RPK Style
postcontent:
Norinco NHM-91 AK47 RPK Style

Up for sale is a NHM91, featuring a stronger receiver and a longer, thicker-profile chrome-lined barrel measuring 20 inches, and comes along with a forward-mounted steel bipod. The bi-pod has never been installed. Also comes with sling and cleaning kit. Comes with 3 mags, a 30 rd, 20, rd and 10 rd. Each one of these mags has a USA made mag follower (counts as 1 USA made part).Now, let’s talk about the changes we did. First we replaced the original wood furniture with a set of original PolyTech AK-47 blonde furniture (Very Rare - at least $250 in value, if you can find a matching set). FYI. The original PolyTech AK-47 parts are NOS (New Old Stock) originally manufactured by Poly Technologies, Inc. of China between 1985 and 1989. These were produced at State Arsenals 416 and 386 during that time.

Next we made the rifle 922 compliant. We replace the fire control group with a USA made Tapco trigger assembly (Counts as 3 USA made parts). Replaced the gas piston with a new USA made Tapco gas piston (counts as 1 USA made part). Next we removed the tac welded muzzle thread protector, replaced the front site detent pin and installed a brand new customized, USA made, muzzle brake (counts as 1 USA made part). Overall in making this rifle 922 compliant, we needed to exchange 6 parts out. So, if we count them up, we now have 6 USA made parts on the gun.

The NHM91 does not come with a scope rail. So, we ordered a relatively new product from Parabellum Armament, their AKARS – adaptive rail system ($130 Value Retail). This will allow you to scope your NHM91 without changing the original config by drilling into the receiver and installing a scope rail. AKARS™—is a weapon upgrade that replaces the rear sight leaf and the receiver’s bolt cover on the Kalashnikov assault rifle. We found that this design is excellent and that field stripping and cleaning does not take away from obtaining zero once you have mounted and dialed in your scope. Included is the original dust cover.

Please make sure your local dealer will accept a firearm from a non-FFL01 dealer for transferring the gun. We are a collector not a dealer.

Ready to ship out, no waiting!!
